{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9c762d5f-206c-4a72-9da0-53fe050aa5a0","content":"This project uses **`packages.config`** format, which is the legacy NuGet package management style. Unfortunately, **Central Package Management (CPM) requires `PackageReference` format** — it cannot work directly with `packages.config` projects.\n\nYou'll need to **migrate from `packages.config` to `PackageReference` first**, then convert to CPM.\n\n**To migrate to PackageReference:**\n1. In **Visual Studio**, right-click `packages.config` → select **\"Migrate packages.config to PackageReference\"**\n2. Or manually:\n   - Remove `packages.config`\n   - Replace the `<Reference>` + `<HintPath>` with `<PackageReference Include=\"Newtonsoft.Json\" Version=\"13.0.3\" />`\n   - Convert the project to SDK-style if possible\n\nWould you like me to perform the manual migration to `PackageReference` format, and then convert to CPM?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7f53c613-6681-43c5-a272-6acf0cf452c2","outputTokens":219},"id":"1fc4ff96-70bd-479c-a421-cfbd767fb93c","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:41:01.094Z","parentId":"10bdb86e-c3f2-45a3-92cc-1e334a897cb3"}
